  <static seed="102" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring355.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{y^{2}-2y+9}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\text{prime}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The number <m>9</m> can be factored into the product of two numbers in the following ways:</p>
<p>\[1(9),-1(-9),3(3),-3(-3)\]</p>
<p>Since no pair<rsq/>s sum is <m>-2</m>, we conclude that this polynomial is <alert>prime</alert>.</p>
</solution>
